August 29, 1969
Dr. John G. Neihardt
Skyrim, R.D. 7
Columbia, Missouri

Dear Dr. Neihardt:
<p>The Editors of Wisdom and I take pleasure in advising you that you have been elected to the Wisdom Hall Of Fame, and we are proud to present you with the 1969 Wisdom Award Of Honor. This high honor, attached herewith, is conferred upon you with our heartfelt appreciation and esteem.</p>
<p>This precious Award eloquently testifies to your being a distinguished and admirable American of high ideals, real intellectual integrity, and true wisdom. It is visual testimony that you are a great believer in the advancement of the human mind and in the highest aspirations of the human spirit. We sincerely hope you will treasure it forever.</p>
<p>Please write and let me know if this Award arrived in perfect condition, and that your name was spelled exactly as you wished. At your convenience, would you send us a brief biographical sketch along with a photograph, which can be anywhere from 8 x 10 to 2 x 2 inches in size. It is for the Wisdom Hall Of Fame special section of The Wisdom Encyclopedia.</p>
<p>God Bless you for helping us plant the precious seeds of Wisdom in many minds, for Wisdom is the power of God in the soul of man. May the spirit of Wisdom always enrich and beautify your life for many glorious years to come.</p>
Faithfully yours,
<signed>Leon Gutterman</signed>
Leon Gutterman
President and Publisher
